lo winners]]\n[[Category:Directors Guild of America Award winners]]\n[[Category:Directors of Palme d'Or winners]]\n[[Category:English-language film directors]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences]]\n[[Category:Film directors from Michigan]]\n[[Category:Golden Globe Award-winning musicians]]\n[[Category:Golden Orange Honorary Award winners]]\n[[Category:Great Neck North High School alumni]]\n[[Category:Hofstra University alumni]]\n[[Category:Horror film directors]]\n[[Category:Jamaica High School (New York City) alumni]]\n[[Category:Michigan Democrats]]\n[[Category:New York Military Academy alumni]]\n[[Category:Officiers of the L\u00e9gion d'honneur]]\n[[Category:Producers who won the Best Picture Academy Award]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Irving G. Thalberg Memorial Award]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Praemium Imperiale]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from Michigan]]\n[[Category:UCLA Film School alumni]]\n[[Category:Viticulturists]]\n[[Category:Writers from Detroit]]\n[[Category:Writers Guild of America Award winners]]\n[[Category:California Democrats]]\n[[Category:Cinema of the San Francisco Bay Area]]\n[[Category:Film directors from California]]\n[[Category:New York (state) Democrats]]\n[[Category:People from Long Island]]\n[[Category:People from the San Francisco Bay Area]]\n[[Category:People from Rutherford, California]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from California]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:People from Woodside, Queens]]\n", "name_user": "Will Sandberg", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Francis_Ford_Coppola"}
{"title_page": "Ashlee Evans-Smith", "text_new": "{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{short description|American mixed martial arts fighter}}\n{{Infobox martial artist\n| name            = Ashlee Evans-Smith\n| other_names     = Bulldog\n| image           = \n| image_size      =\n| alt             = \n| caption         =\n| birth_name      =\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1987|7|9}}\n| birth_place     = [[Ukiah, California]]\n| death_date      = \n| death_place     =\n| death_cause     =\n| residence       = \n| nationality     = [[United States|American]]\n| height          = {{height|ft=5|in=8}}\n| weight          =\n {{convert|135|lb|kg st|abbr=on}}\n| weight_class    = [[Flyweight (MMA)|Flyweight]]  <br> [[Bantamweight (MMA)|Bantamweight]] <br>  [[Featherweight (MMA)|Featherweight]]\n| reach_in        = 67\n| style           = \n| stance          = \n| fighting_out_of = \n| team            = \n| rank            = Blue belt in [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]]<ref name=UFCprofile>{{cite web|url=http://www.ufc.com/fighter/ashlee-evans-smith|title=Ashlee Evans-Smith - Official UFC Fighter Profile|publisher=UFC.com|accessdate=September 4, 2016}}</ref>\n| wrestling       = \n| university      = [[Menlo College]]\n| school          = \n| years_active    = \n| mma_kowin       = 3\n| mma_subwin      = \n| mma_decwin      = 3\n| mma_dqwin       = \n| mma_koloss      = \n| mma_subloss     = 2\n| mma_decloss     = 2\n| mma_draw        = \n| mma_nc          = \n| url             =\n| sherdog         = 75021\n| footnotes       =\n| updated         =\n}}\n'''Ashlee Evans-Smith''' (born July 9, 1987) is an American mixed martial artist who competes in the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]]'s women's flyweight division.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2016/08/ufc-fight-night-93s-ashlee-evans-smith-ive-been-thrown-to-the-wolves-but-ive-risen-to-the-occasion|title=UFC Fight Night 93's Ashlee Evans-Smith: 'I've been thrown to the wolves, but I've risen to the occasion'|date=31 August 2016|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==MMA career==\nAs an amateur, Ashlee Evans-Smith had a record of 5-4 and is the former Tuff-N-Uff Champion. Her four losses were against women with a combined amateur record of 20-1-1. She also has a notable victory over former UFC fighter [[Jessamyn Duke]].\n\nEvans-Smith began her professional career on March 2, 2013, in the quarterfinals for the CFA Women's PGA Tournament. In an arduous battle, full of twists, against her former amateur rival, Tori Adams, Evans-Smith won by unanimous decision, thus avenging a past loss.\n\nShe was then scheduled to fight [[Peggy Morgan]] in the semi-final round at CFA 11 but was removed from the card after auditioning for [[The Ultimate Fighter: Team Rousey vs. Team Tate|TUF 18]]. A recent report from The Wrestling Observer Newsletter announced that Evans-Smith was one of the 17 fighters selected for TUF 18 but at age 25, instead preferred to regain her place in the CFA tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fightersonlymag.com/content/news/18861-report-female-tuf-18-participants-named|archive-url=https://archive.today/20160415192115/http://www.fightersonlymag.com/content/news/18861-report-female-tuf-18-participants-named|url-status=dead|archive-date=15 April 2016|title=Report: Female TUF 18 participants named - Fighters Only Magazine|accessdate=13 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nEvans-Smith automatically advanced to the finals because Morgan was removed from the tournament. Then news surfaced that she would face transgender fighter [[Fallon Fox]] because Morgan's opponent, Anna Barone, could not make the weight.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmarising.com/news/2013/05/10/ashlee-evans-smith-now-set-to-face-anna-barone-at-cfa-11/|title=Ashlee Evans-Smith Now Set To Face Anna Barone At CFA 11 - MMARising.com|first=|last=MMARising.com|publisher=|accessdate=13 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Fox vs. Evans-Smith===\n\nOn October 12, 2013, Evans-Smith made it to the finals of the CFA 12 tournament, entering as a heavy underdog, reaching +425 in the bookmakers' odds. After a back-and-forth first round, she started taking over in the second round. The round ended in controversy because while Evans-Smith was applying punches from the top position, the referee failed to hear the signal announcing the end of the round, so she continued to beat on [[Fallon Fox]]. The referee called the fight a TKO in her favor when the round should have already been over. As Ashlee, her corner and the crowd celebrated, the referee informed her that he had made a mistake, and the fight would go to a third round. In the 3rd, Ashlee was able to get the top position again and managed to hit a wave of punches, until the referee intervened and stopped the fight, giving her the win by TKO in the third round.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bloodyelbow.com/2013/10/14/4839074/ufc-fighters-react-to-fallon-foxs-tko-loss-to-ashlee-evans-smith-mma-news|title=Fighters react to Fallon Fox's first loss|first=|last=ShinSplints|date=15 October 2013|publisher=Bloody Elbow}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2013/10/ashlee-evans-smith-had-love-hate-relationship-with-fallon-fox-controversy|title=Ashlee Evans-Smith had 'love-hate relationship' with Fallon Fox controversy|date=22 October 2013|publisher=MMA Junkie}}</ref>\n\n===WSOF===\n\nEvans-Smith then signed with the [[World Series of Fighting]] to fight Marciea Allen at [[World Series of Fighting 10: Branch vs. Taylor|WSOF 10]]. She won the bout by technical knockout in the third round.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmaweekly.com/wsof-10-fight-highlights-video-ashlee-evans-smith-vs-marciea-allen|title=WSOF 10 Fight Highlights Video: Ashlee Evans-Smith vs. Marciea Allen - MMAWeekly.com|publisher=|accessdate=13 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Ultimate Fighting Championship===\n\nWith a perfect 3-0 record, Evans-Smith had the first opportunity in the organization to fight [[Raquel Pennington]] on December 6, 2014, at [[UFC 181]] following a neck injury to Pennington's original opponent [[Holly Holm]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2014/11/ashlee-evans-smith-replaces-holly-holm-at-ufc-181-in-las-vegas|title=Ashlee Evans-Smith replaces Holly Holm at UFC 181 in Las Vegas|date=19 November 2014|publisher=}}</ref> The fight was balanced and \"locked,\" especially at the clinch, until Pennington secured a bulldog choke at the end of the round. When the round was over, it was revealed that Evans-Smith was unconscious due to the finish. The fight was interrupted between rounds 1 and 2, however, the official time is 4:59 of the first round. Ashlee soon after was suspended for diuretic use.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2015/02/why-nsac-took-action-with-ashlee-evans-smith-and-issued-suspension-fine|title=Why NSAC took action with Ashlee Evans-Smith and issued suspension, fine|date=18 February 2015|publisher=MMA Junkie}}</ref>\n\nEvans-Smith faced [[Veronica Macedo]] on September 3, 2016, at [[UFC Fight Night 93]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fight24.pl/veronica-macedo-vs-ashlee-evans-smith-na-ufc-fight-night-93/|title=Veronica Macedo vs. Ashlee Evans-Smith na UFC Fight Night 93 {{!}} FIGHT24.PL - MMA i K-1, UFC|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref> She won the fight via technical knockout in round three.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mmajunkie.com/2016/09/video-watch-ashlee-evans-smith-drop-hellacious-elbow-bombs-on-veronica-macedo-for-tko|title=Watch how Ashlee Evans-Smith took out Veronica Macedo with nasty elbows at UFC Fight Night 93|date=2016-09-03|website=MMAjunkie|language=en|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref>\n\nEvans-Smith faced [[Sarah Moras]] on September 9, 2017, at [[UFC 215]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mymmanews.com/ashlee-evans-smith-vs-sarah-moras/|title=Ashlee Evans-Smith vs. Sarah Moras set for UFC 216 in Canada|date=2017-06-07|work=My MMA News.com|access-date=2017-08-24|language=en-US}}</ref> She lost the fight via armbar submission, resulting in her elbow being dislocated,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2732617-sarah-cheesecake-dislocates-opponents-elbow-with-ufc-215-armbar|title=Sarah 'Cheesecake' Moras Dislocates Opponent's Elbow with UFC 215 Armbar|last=Ryder|first=Matthew|work=Bleacher Report|access-date=2017-09-12|language=en-US}}</ref> in the first round.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2017/09/ufc-215-results-sarah-moras-cranks-ashlee-evans-smith-arm|title=UFC 215 results: Sarah Moras cranks Ashlee Evans-Smith's arm for first-round win|date=2017-09-10|work=MMAjunkie|access-date=2017-09-10|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nEvans-Smith faced [[Bec Rawlings]] on April 7, 2018, at [[UFC 223]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2018/02/ashlee-evans-smith-flyweight-bec-rawlings-ufc-223-mma|title=Ashlee Evans-Smith drops to flyweight, meets Bec Rawlings at UFC 223|date=2018-02-04|work=MMAjunkie|access-date=2018-02-04|language=en-US}}</ref> She won the fight by unanimous decision.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2018/04/ufc-223-results-ashlee-evans-smith-bec-rawlings-unanimous-decision-brooklyn-new-york|title=UFC 223 results: Ashlee Evans-Smith outworks Bec Rawlings for decision sweep|date=2018-04-08|work=MMAjunkie|access-date=2018-04-08|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nEvans-Smith was expected to face promotional newcomer [[Antonina Shevchenko]] on November 30, 2018, at [[The Ultimate Fighter: Heavy Hitters#The Ultimate Fighter 28 Finale|The Ultimate Fighter 28 Finale]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmadna.nl/ufc-debutanten-don-madge-en-te-edwards-vechten-tijdens-ufc-moncton/|title=Ashlee Evans-Smith vs. Antonina Shevchenko at the TUF 28 Finale in Las Vegas|publisher=mmadna.nl|author=Marcel Dorff|date=2018-09-06|accessdate=2018-09-06|language=nl}}</ref> However, it was reported on 8 November 2018 that Evans-Smith pulled out of the event due to injury and she was replaced by [[Ji Yeon Kim]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/2018/11/8/18076130/antonina-shevchenko-gets-new-opponent-at-tuf-28-finale-with-ashlee-evans-smith-out|title=Antonina Shevchenko gets new opponent at TUF 28 Finale with Ashlee Evans-Smith out|website=mmafighting.com|author=Marc Raimondi|date=2018-11-08|accessdate=2018-11-08}}</ref>\n\nEvans-Smith was scheduled to face Lauren Murphy on February 17, 2019, at [[UFC on ESPN: Ngannou vs. Velasquez|UFC on ESPN 1]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mmadna.nl/lauren-murphy-treft-ashlee-evans-smith-tijdens-ufc-on-espn-1-in-phoenix/|title=Lauren Murphy treft Ashlee Evans-Smith tijdens UFC on ESPN 1 in Phoenix|last=DNA|first=MMA|language=en-US|access-date=2018-12-06}}</ref> However on December 19, 2018, Murphy announced and withdraw from the event as she would need more time off to recover from foot surgery. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/2018/12/19/18149191/lauren-murphy-withdraws-from-ufc-on-espn-fight-vs-ashlee-evans-smith-to-recover-from-surgery|title=Lauren Murphy withdraws from UFC on ESPN fight vs. Ashlee Evans-Smith to recover from surgery|last=Newswire|first=MMA Fighting|date=2018-12-19|website=MMA Fighting|access-date=2018-12-20}}</ref> On December 20, it was reported that [[Andrea Lee (fighter)|Andrea Lee]] will replace Murphy against Evans-Smith.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mymmanews.com/andrea-lee-vs-ashlee-evans-smith/|title=Andrea Lee in for Lauren Murphy vs. Ashlee Evans-Smith at UFC on ESPN 1|publisher=mymmanews.com|author=Mike Heck|date=2018-12-20|access-date=2018-12-21}}</ref> Evans-Smith lost the fight by unanimous decision.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mmajunkie.com/2019/02/ufc-on-espn-1-results-andrea-lee-too-much-for-ashlee-evans-smith-impresses-in-decision-win|title=UFC on ESPN 1 results: Andrea Lee too much for Ashlee Evans-Smith, impresses in decision win|date=2019-02-18|website=MMAjunkie|language=en|access-date=2019-02-18}}</ref>\n\nEvans-Smith was expected to face Taila Santos on August 10, 2019, at [[UFC on ESPN+ 14]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mmadna.nl/ashlee-evans-smith-vs-taila-santos-toegevoegd-aan-ufc-montevideo/|title=Ashlee Evans-Smith vs. Taila Santos added to UFC Montevideo|author=Marcel Dorff|publisher=mmadnanl.com|date=2019-05-29|access-date=2019-05-29|language=nl}}</ref> However, Evans-Smith withdrew the bout for undisclosed reasons.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sherdog.com/news/news/Report-Ashlee-EvansSmith-Out-Ariane-Carnelossi-In-Against-Taila-Santos-at-UFC-Uruguay-157865|title=Report: Ashlee Evans-Smith Out, Ariane Carnelossi In Against Taila Santos at UFC Uruguay|last=Sherdog.com|website=Sherdog|access-date=2019-08-07}}</ref>\n\nEvans-Smith was scheduled to face [[Molly McCann]] on March 21, 2020 at [[UFC Fight Night 171]].<ref name=\"Mollyvs.Ashley\">{{Cite web|url=https://mmadna.nl/thuisgevecht-voor-molly-mccann-tegen-ashlee-evans-smith-tijdens-ufc-londen/|title=Home fight for Molly McCann against Ashlee Evans-Smith during UFC London|author=Redactie|publisher=mmadna.com|access-date=2019-12-05}}{{in lang|nl}}</ref> Due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], the event was eventually postponed .<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mmajunkie.usatoday.com/2020/03/ufc-postpones-three-events-coronavirus-pandemic|title=UFC postpones three events amid growing coronavirus outbreak|publisher=mmajunkie.usatoday.com|author=Nolan King and John Morgan|date=2020-03-15|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\n==Mixed martial arts record==\n{{MMArecordbox\n|draws=\n|nc=\n|ko-wins=3\n|ko-losses=\n|sub-wins=\n|sub-losses=2\n|dec-wins=3\n|dec-losses=2\n|dq-wins=\n|dq-losses=\n}}\n{{MMA record start}}\n|-\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|align=center|6\u20134\n|[[Andrea Lee (fighter)|Andrea Lee]]\n|Decision (unanimous)\n|[[UFC on ESPN: Ngannou vs. Velasquez]]\n|{{dts|2019|February|17}}\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|5:00\n|[[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]], Arizona, United States\n|\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|align=center|6\u20133\n|[[Bec Rawlings]]\n|Decision (unanimous)\n|[[UFC 223]]\n|{{dts|2018|April|7}}\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|5:00\n|[[Brooklyn, New York|Brooklyn]], New York, United States\n|{{small|Flyweight debut.}}\n|-\n|{